        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> With regards to the video sent by @schilkp and the particular example of compiling LaTeX (while a feature that I would like as well) it seems strange that a text editor would ship with, or depend on, a LaTeX compiler. Suggesting to me that this particular feature would be better suited to being a plugin rather than a part of the core program.\n\n\nJust to be clear - my suggestion was not that NVIM should support this out of the box, but rather I was providing an example of the \"plugins are encouraged to build upon this\" point in the original post:\n\nThere are already plugins that do such inline previews, and they usually have dedicated mechanisms for showing/hiding them. I just thought it would be cool if there was a  system-level notion of \"presentation mode\" vs \"edit mode\" that could be used to control all such preview plugins. ",
